value: Breeds throughout the greater part of the eastern half of North America (west to about the middle of the Great Plains) from southern Alberta, southern Saskatchewan, southern Manitoba, southern On- tario, the St. Lawrence valley and Nova Scotia south to southern Texas, the Gulf Coast and Florida. Winters from middle Florida and Louisiana through southern Mexico and Central America to Panama; occurs casually in Cuba, Hispaniola, the Bahama Islands and Bermuda.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Deciduous or mixed woodland, second growth, parks, and open situations with scattered trees, foraging also in meadows and gardens; in migration and winter, a wide variety of woodland and open habitats.
